<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="588" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d588">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Pera</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-02"><hi rend="italic">October 2,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Monday several hundred Armenians marched on the Porte professedly to ask
                            redress of grievances. The patriarch tried to prevent it. A conflict
                            occurred between Armenians and police. Probably about 60 Turks and
                            Armenians killed—among others Turkish major—and many wounded. Armenians
                            carried pistols. Yesterday several more were killed. Last night 80
                            killed. Several hundred imprisoned. Porte had notice of the
                            demonstration, which they say was organized by leaders of Huntchaguist
                            revolutionists, whom they have captured. Much terror exists. I think
                            Porte will be able to restrain fanaticism.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>